  "prompt": "Why do I see numbers and not contacts' names? In WhatsApp?",
  "response": "If you are seeing phone numbers instead of contact names in WhatsApp, it could be due to several reasons:\n\n1. **Contacts Not Saved**: The phone numbers are not saved in your phone's contact list. Ensure that the numbers are saved with the correct names in your device's contacts.\n\n2. **Permissions**: WhatsApp may not have permission to access your contacts. Check your phone\u2019s settings to make sure WhatsApp has the necessary permissions to read your contacts.\n\n3. **Sync Issues**: There might be a sync issue between your phone\u2019s contact list and WhatsApp. Try refreshing or re-syncing your contacts.\n\n4. **Account Issues**: You might be logged into a different account that doesn\u2019t have access to your saved contacts.\n\n5. **Updates**: Ensure that WhatsApp is updated to the latest version. An outdated version might cause display issues.\n\n6. **Cache Issues**: Sometimes, clearing the cache of the WhatsApp app can resolve display problems. Go to your phone settings and clear the app cache.\n\nIf none of these solutions work, you might want to contact WhatsApp support for further assistance.",
